The forces of the giant strike are gathering
The Liga Unions and the National Federation of Workers’ Commissions will constitute on Friday a strike commission to coordinate Monday’s strike that will last indefinitely.
A protest rally will be held on Saturday, while on Monday - the day on which the final vote on the public health law will be held - the work stoppage will begin.
This action will surely cause great difficulties in transport, since rail traffic will completely stop and until 13 hours will also be on strike the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company.
On Friday afternoon, the League Unions will report on the details of their strike on Monday that will be held jointly with the National Federation of Workers’ Commissions.
Likewise, the strike commission of the LIGA and the National Union of Drivers will be constituted that will coordinate the actions on Monday.
On Saturday, a rally will be held, while on Monday the participating unions will pronounce themselves on strike indefinitely, if no agreement is reached with the government.
This means that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law - they did not report on the date of the end of the strike initiated.
If the National Assembly disapproves of the public health law, the unions will immediately withdraw their call for strike.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, strike commissions will meet and decide on the future.
Based on the Monday agenda of the National Assembly it is also possible that only the public health law will be voted on in the very early hours of the night, or perhaps near midnight.
As a result of the strike that will begin on Monday, significant difficulties in transport will have to be had: in the railways you will stop working indefinitely, by the morning you may stop a part of the collective transport of Budapest and more than half of the intercity transport of buses of the Volán companies.
Simultaneously, in many parts of the country there will be closure of half of the roads.
Numerous trade unions and civil organizations have joined the strike, their names are constantly updated on the League’s website.
Some unions announced their strike indefinitely, others in definite time.
Until Thursday afternoon the State Railway and the Free Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) could not reach an agreement even on minimum services, although, as the Christmas holidays approach, more and more people are traveling on trains.
According to information received until now, from the beginning of the day until 13 hours will be striked the workers of the Collective Transport Company of Budapest, those of Budapest Airport from 7 to 9 in the morning, will hold a four-hour strike the LIGA Unions of the Electricity Industry and Thermal Energy, the Unions of the Educators called for a strike of 2 and the Democratic Union of the Educators from 2 to 8 hours.
The Hungarian Association of Physicians will speak on a national strike at alternative times and the Democratic Union of Health and Social Workers (SDTSSS) that are part of the Trade Union Cooperation Forum, will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands made by the League is that the government withdraw its proposal for public health reform and submit a new conception to a social debate.
The second demand is for them to gradually introduce the new way of calculating pensions that will come into effect next year.
The third is that they ensure, even before 2010, for the case of advance pensions the possibility that the occupations that deserve it can enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Railway Workers Union (SLTF), which is part of the League Unions, do not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport on the railway sidelines and expect another different proposal.
Political Capital: The country increases the risk by the Hungarian Guard
According to the Risk Analysis Division of the Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, established in August of this year with the support of the Movement for a Better Hungary, from several points of view the political risk of Hungary and the region has increased.
In the "risk warning" of the company it is written: in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard the greatest political risk is the fact that "with the aggravation of the ethnic tensions between the Roma and non-Gypsy people of Hungary, even in the short term there may be violent ethnic confrontations."
The main reason for this is that the Hungarian Guard’s political strategy is probably the provocation of an event of this nature – added the representative of the research institute.
They affirmed that all this is due to one of the main faults of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life gave the public debate of the Roma problem to the representatives of the radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the discrepancies between Gypsies and Hungarians."
This aggravates the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflicts - they estimate.
In addition to that, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international average, "significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, especially with regard to the stability and democratic development of the country."
They remind us that: from the autumn of 2006 it received increasing publicity and momentum the reorganization of the radical and far-right groups of Hungary and that since the summer of 2007 numerous organizations have been constituted in the country that define themselves as "national self-defense associations".
