The party is not always written with red numbers
In Hungary the law precisely defines the days that are written with red numbers on the calendar and has already become a widespread practice that around the holidays - that the coming year will be less - the working hours are reorganized.
Even in the EU or in North America are the holidays unitary.
Hungarian laws make a difference between national holiday, state holiday and festive days.
The holidays are fundamentally related to religious festivals and historical events.
We celebrate the New Year also: both the last day of the old year, and the first day of the new year is a holiday - the latter above all so that those who spent celebrating the old year can rest.
Throughout the year we have eleven parties written with red numbers on the calendar.
It is a national holiday on March 15 in memory of the revolution of 1848 and October 23, the commemorative day of the 1956 revolution.
On August 20 we celebrate the foundation of the State, on May 1st the party of work, on November 1 and 2 we remember our family and deceased friends.
In addition, in our country are two-day feasts Easter, Pentecost and Christmas.
According to the calendar, our state, national or religious holidays rarely coincide with a weekend, so it is often bridged when before or after the party there is a single workday.
In exchange for the extended weekends like this, during the previous Saturdays you can not be absent from work or school.
He is the minister of work who regulates in his specific decree when it is necessary to work exactly in exchange for the day directly preceding or after the feast.
This legal standard is mandatory for all employers and their employees, as well as for employees and public officials.
It is not mandatory instead for companies and service institutions that, due to their role, work uninterruptedly even during the holidays.
This year the order of work can be altered only around the holidays of the end of the year: from December 24 practically the life in the country stops, since according to the experiences, most people "bridge" during the days between Christmas and the end of the year or take their holidays during these days.
The next year several of our parties will coincide with mid or weekends, so there will be fewer changes in working hours than this year.
First the agenda around the work party will be modified so that then, for four successive days, the workers can rest.
Saturday, April 26 will be working day, so that in return Friday, May 2 is a holiday.
The other change is related to the feast of October 23: on Saturday, October 18, you will have to work instead of Friday 24.
On the other hand, the year that comes during the end of year party can rest, since from December 24 will not be worked on almost anywhere, or even if the last day of the year is a Wednesday.
