Congress approves the transposition of the Mifid, which came into force 1 November
In parallel with its parliamentary process, which ended today with the vote by the Congress of the amendments incorporated into the bill in the Senate, the Government has submitted to public hearing the regulation that will develop the new law, with the aim of getting both into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the different groups agreed to highlight the effort made by deputies and senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulation in order to guarantee the protection of investors and regulate in detail the activity of the entities so that the markets work efficiently.
The Mifid, which amends the Securities Market Act, involves the modernisation of financial markets, while strengthening investor protection, improving the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and fostering cooperation between the various supervisors of the European Union.
The new regulation will provide financial advisory services to both specialized firms and natural or legal persons and creates a new type of financial services firms (ESIS), financial advisory companies (AFIs), which join securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it expands the number of systems for the execution of transactions on financial instruments, so that regulated secondary markets are joined by multilateral trading systems and internalization of orders systems, which will compete with current stock exchange managers.
