Currently the wooden boxes produced in Sweden are like the shadow that weighs on Warhol’s list of works.
Most of the ninety-four "type" Brillio-Box on this list are fake.
After a few months ago the Swedish newspaper "Expressen" put the doubt about the authenticity of Brillo-Boxes of the year 1968 of Andy Warhol, the Museum Moderna Museet in Stockholm carried out internal research and reached disappointing conclusions: the six "Brillo-Boxes", which the former director of the museum Pontus Hultén gave to the museum Moderna Museet, are false, and almost one hundred of the others of "type"
Prehistory is too complicated with a confusing relationship between artistic and sponsored productions.
In 1964 Warhol created in New York his first "Brightness-Boxes", he painted the wooden boxes of red, blue and white, with the same sample that they had "Glow" soap powder cartons.
According to Warhol, hundreds of cardboard boxes were exhibited in the exhibition of his 1968 works at the Moderna Museet museum. These were not made by Warhol (because of the expenses), but were brought directly from the "Brightness" cardboard factory.
These were not works of art, but of specimens (which were only objects) on display.
In the same year, 1968, Warhol allowed to produce in Sweden some Bright-wooden boxes, but they were not exhibited in the Modern Museet museum.
Witnesses of those times now speak of the fact that almost fifteen boxes, which at that time entered the history of art and auctions as originals of the "Boxes" of "Stockhol-type" authorized by Andy Warhol.
In auctions some of them were bought for more than 100 000 dollars.
The problem is that after the famous director of the Pontus Hultén museum made false statements that in 1968 in Sweden were produced and exposed almost a hundred of the wooden boxes that Warhol left to him.
But in reality, 105 boxes were produced in the same year 1990 in Malmö for Hultén and for the exhibition in St. Petersburg.
At this time Warhol had already died for 3 years.
Lars Byström, the head of the curators of the Moderna Museet museum, investigated six museum-owned Brillio-Boxes and also three of the Swedish private property that were manufactured in 1968 in Stockholm. First they printed and fraded their tight silvers and then painted them in oil with the brush.
On the contrary, the structure of the 1990 copies shows that the paint was applied with a roller without directly printing the tight silvers. In addition, it is not about oil painting, but about acrylic painting.
“These boxes have not been authorized by the artist and must be removed from Andy Warhol’s official Brillio-Boxes list,” says Lars Nittve, the director of the Moderna Museet museum and adds that if The “Andy Warhol Art” Authentication Commission in New York will not come to any conclusion, the Moderna Museet museum will classify these six boxes as the exhibition copies/objects.”
Already in July the Authentication Commission formally announced that it accepts these "serious accusations" in which it is boxes of soap powder.
But from that moment there everything remained in absolute silence.
The rebel soldiers surrender in Manila.
In the Philippines, rebel soldiers have surrendered to a hotel in Manila and demanded the fall of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
The ringleader Antonio Trillanes, who reproaches the president, corruption and electoral fraud, told a reporter that she could not answer for shedding blood.
Soldiers loyal to the government had raided the hotel using tear gas.
Almost two hundred soldiers had been barricading themselves in the building for a few hours.
Almost half of them, including Trillanes, were on trial Thursday for trying a 2003 coup that ended in failure.
He took advantage of the negotiations, so suddenly he could deposit himself with about 30 supporters.
Evidently the military policemen who were to watch him had passed into their ranks and followed his mutiny.
They entered the hotel "Peninsula" and demanded the fall of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
Government troops blocked the neighborhood around the Noble Hotel.
The president called for an urgent session of the Security Cabinet.
Norberto Gonzales, the National Security Councilor, condemned the soldiers’ behavior.
"People are fed up," Trillanes said.
"We call people to get to our ranks."
General Danilo Lim, who previously led the elite Scout Reangers troops, said that soon the other military troops wanted to follow the march.
Big critics of government on Thursday called for a large demonstration against the president.
For months, his government has been rebuked for corruption.
In 2003 the financial district in Manila was a site that attracted all the attention for the mutiny that was attempted against Arroyo.
The uprising failed after about 24 hours because the army wanted to participate.
Since 1986 in the Philippines there have been at least seven coup attempts against democratically elected government.
United Internet will be Versatel’s largest shareholder.
United Internet secured more than 20 percent of the shares of telecommunications company Versatel.
On Wednesday the company reported that the average price for a share is 14, 46 euros.
You have only 20.05 percent of the share capital.
There was a lot of speculation about the company’s absorption.
There are also options to further increase the financial part in Versatel.
United Internet reported that with this step it wants to accelerate the consolidation of the German market of DSL (Digital Subscriber Line).
On Wednesday they already made assumptions about entry into the business, after Brendenberg bank increased its stake to Duesseldorf’s network operator by 5 percent to 15.1 percent.
In the financial market that means that the financial institution maintains the equity for a third party.
United Internet already in the previous day made the telecom company Drillisch participate with almost 10 percent.
Drillisch in the measure of capital increase placed 17.4 million of new shares that are worth 106.4 million euros.
United Internet has purchased 5.15 million shares for 31.4 million euros.
In addition, the companies started negotiations on marketing cooperations for DSL-products.
"Let's strengthen our collaboration," United Internet spokesman said.
The two companies founded a company together MSP, to acquire competitor Freenet.
On Thursday, United Internet reported that at the beginning, the two companies want to be happy with the ten percent stake in Freenet and do not use their right, that is, they make 18.49 per hundreds of Freenet participate.
That meant that both companies kept all the options, especially the participation to the Freenet corporation.
The negotiations between United Internet and Freenet on a strategic partnership ended in mid-November.
This "game" with Freenet that will last for many months and is not very understandable is part of the consolidation of the German Telecom market.
At the end of the third quarter, Freenet had 2.9 million customers with a mobile phone contract and 1.27 million with a DSL contract or a full contract.
Until now, the United Internet and Drillisch holding company directly had 6.01 percent of the stake in Freenet.
They had then agreed that Drillisch will achieve the other four percent.
The right to buy 18.49 percent of the Vatas investment company was already agreed in August.
